18:18.545 --> 18:19.486
He will help me.

18:19.526 --> 18:22.330
I will look triumphant over those who hate me.

18:22.390 --> 18:25.454
Yes, sometimes you will have haters in your life.

18:26.315 --> 18:31.301
Sometimes you have people that won't like you, but that doesn't matter because God loves you.

18:31.341 --> 18:33.023
Amen.

18:33.303 --> 18:34.985
So don't worry about the people.

18:35.005 --> 18:41.674
Don't be concerned about the people that don't like you because God will bring good people around that will love you.

18:41.714 --> 18:45.138
I'm glad I got a loving congregation that loves me.

18:45.730 --> 18:46.691
Lord of God.

18:48.534 --> 18:54.963
And it says in Psalms 118, 8 through 9, it says, it's better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in people.

18:55.444 --> 18:59.209
It's better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes is.

19:00.010 --> 19:03.074
And so sometimes we put our trust in people.

19:03.114 --> 19:04.216
Pastors can do that.

19:04.877 --> 19:09.303
Pastors can put their trust in the numbers of people that show up on Sunday morning.

19:09.343 --> 19:11.947
If that number doesn't hit, the pastor gets nervous.

19:12.688 --> 19:12.988
Amen?

19:13.389 --> 19:14.290
But you know what?

19:14.434 --> 19:17.759
The pastor doesn't need to put his faith in the numbers.

19:17.799 --> 19:19.361
He needs to put his faith in God.

19:19.401 --> 19:20.663
I'm preaching to myself today.

19:20.723 --> 19:29.336
I'm preaching to myself today because God is my source and the church isn't my source.

19:29.356 --> 19:31.219
You're not my source.

19:31.239 --> 19:32.241
God's my source.

19:33.162 --> 19:33.543
Amen.

19:33.903 --> 19:43.858
And so I'm going to say this as long as I'm doing what I'm supposed to be doing, God's going to get the blessing to me, regardless of what's happening in the church.

19:44.450 --> 19:45.411
Do you believe that today?

19:45.952 --> 19:48.635
Somebody say I'm blessed to be a blessing.

19:49.836 --> 19:51.358
Amen, you're blessed to be a blessing.

19:51.378 --> 19:55.443
So we see here that we know at times people can let us down.

19:55.723 --> 19:57.946
Has anybody ever let you down in your life?

19:59.828 --> 20:03.713
You said my spouse just this morning, right?

20:04.053 --> 20:08.138
And then some people, have you ever had friends that abandoned you?

20:08.859 --> 20:11.442
Have you ever had people that abandoned you?

20:11.746 --> 20:13.428
or left you, amen?

20:13.528 --> 20:14.470
High and dry.

20:14.510 --> 20:15.151
Have you ever heard that?

20:15.171 --> 20:16.332
They left me high.

20:16.352 --> 20:17.514
I don't know what that means.

20:17.995 --> 20:21.580
High and dry, but they left me high and dry.

20:22.160 --> 20:24.303
Pastor, you don't know what they did to me.

20:24.423 --> 20:26.166
You don't know how they treated me.

20:26.707 --> 20:29.130
Yeah, but God's treating you much better, amen?

20:30.051 --> 20:33.496
And then have you ever had anybody turn against you?

20:33.536 --> 20:36.740
Amen.

20:36.760 --> 20:38.303
I've got to laugh out there, amen?

20:39.064 --> 20:40.786
Sometimes you have people

20:40.898 --> 20:42.700
that, you know, think about this.

20:42.860 --> 20:45.143
Jesus had people turn against him.

20:45.904 --> 20:47.546
And Jesus walked in love.

20:48.447 --> 20:49.649
I mean, think about Jesus.

20:49.709 --> 20:51.711
I mean, the perfect one, right?

20:52.072 --> 20:58.300
I mean, if anybody should, if anybody should be sold out to Jesus, never do anything bad for Jesus.

20:58.320 --> 21:01.323
Cause Jesus always did good to people.

21:01.744 --> 21:03.626
Jesus had people banning him.

21:04.007 --> 21:06.770
Jesus had Judas betray him.

21:07.426 --> 21:11.251
Think about this, Jesus had it all, he had all of this, but you know what?

21:11.772 --> 21:19.782
The Bible says Jesus knew what was in men's hearts and he didn't put his trust in men, but he put his trust in God.

21:21.624 --> 21:27.131
And you gotta put your trust in God no matter how men is treating you.

21:27.852 --> 21:29.134
Say I'm trusting God.

21:30.235 --> 21:30.556
Amen.

21:30.996 --> 21:35.442
And so I'm gonna say this, point number one, God will never let you down

21:35.682 --> 21:38.285
but he will bring you up in your time of need.

21:38.825 --> 21:42.950
God will never let you down and he will bring you up in your time of need.

21:42.970 --> 21:45.232
In other words, he will get you out of your problem.

21:45.833 --> 21:46.794
Do you believe that today?

21:46.814 --> 21:57.185
It's Psalms 34, it says, I sought the Lord and he answered me and he delivered me from all my fears.

21:57.746 --> 21:58.787
So what's the key?

21:59.207 --> 22:05.234
Well, the key is when you're encountering a trial or a tribulation in your life, seek

22:05.314 --> 22:06.195
the Lord.

22:07.196 --> 22:08.778
Don't run from him.

22:08.818 --> 22:10.280
Run to him.

22:10.340 --> 22:13.564
Don't run to your fix.

22:14.204 --> 22:16.367
Some people have a fix.

22:16.387 --> 22:17.108
What do I mean by that?

22:17.428 --> 22:22.093
Well, they run to something that they meditate or medicate their problem.

22:22.614 --> 22:26.799
It could be alcohol or drugs, but run to Jesus.

22:27.820 --> 22:29.762
Even Christians can do those things.

22:29.862 --> 22:32.946
Amen, but run to Jesus.

22:33.026 --> 22:40.157
because those things are temporary fixes but long-term misery.

22:40.718 --> 22:41.519
Do you believe that today?

22:42.460 --> 22:46.226
Number two, God will never abandon you like people will do at times.

22:46.426 --> 22:46.767
Amen?

22:47.347 --> 22:51.934
I like what he says in Deuteronomy 31, 8, the Lord himself goes before you.

22:51.954 --> 22:52.856
I love that.

22:52.956 --> 23:00.086
God is going before you and he will be with you and he will never leave you nor forsake you.

23:00.107 --> 23:02.450
Do not be afraid.

23:02.530 --> 23:05.433
Do not be discouraged.

23:05.453 --> 23:06.694
What is the devil trying to do?

23:06.714 --> 23:08.236
He's trying to discourage some of us.

23:09.176 --> 23:10.658
I'm not going to be discouraged.

23:10.778 --> 23:12.339
I'm going to be encouraged.

23:13.100 --> 23:13.801
Glory to God.

23:14.221 --> 23:23.450
And then God will not turn against you at times even when you are lacking faith because he is faithful in keeping his promises.

23:23.771 --> 23:31.538
Have you ever been out here and have you ever been in a trial of your life and you felt like that you weren't going to make it?

23:31.714 --> 23:33.536
I think all of us been there.

23:34.197 --> 23:36.799
And your faith has been getting rocked.

23:37.060 --> 23:38.982
Has your faith ever been rocked out here?

23:39.883 --> 23:43.266
I'm not talking about rock to sleep, amen?

23:43.386 --> 23:45.689
I'm talking about getting a little unsteady.

23:45.769 --> 23:48.452
Have you ever been unsteady in your faith?

23:48.972 --> 23:55.139
Well, we know we've all been there at times, but where faith doesn't get you there, God's mercy will.

23:56.340 --> 23:58.482
So where we can't get it with faith,

23:58.562 --> 24:00.885
God's mercy will come into our lives.

24:01.185 --> 24:02.126
Do you believe that today?

24:02.827 --> 24:12.839
And I like what it says in 2 Timothy 2, 13, if we are faithless, he remains faithful for he cannot disown himself.

24:12.899 --> 24:13.620
What's that saying?

24:13.920 --> 24:16.343
That sometimes we're not as faithful as we need to be.

24:16.383 --> 24:20.488
Sometimes we're not doing it all right as we need to be.

24:20.928 --> 24:25.874
But even if we're not, God remains faithful anyway.

24:26.402 --> 24:28.385
because God cannot deny Himself.

24:28.506 --> 24:38.443
Like what it says in 1 Corinthians 1 9, God is faithful who has called you into fellowship with His Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.

24:38.723 --> 24:41.668
He's faithful who's called us into fellowship.

24:41.828 --> 24:42.169
Amen?

24:42.650 --> 24:49.922
And so this is key because God initiates the fellowship with us, glory to God.

24:50.403 --> 24:52.146
So we have to put our trust and hope

24:52.546 --> 24:56.593
in God and not people because people will let you down.

24:56.693 --> 24:56.994
Amen?

24:57.435 --> 25:04.307
When I'm dealing with fear in my life and every once in a while, yes, even the pastor deals with fear every once in a while.

25:05.048 --> 25:08.254
And when I'm doing fear, I lock into some scriptures.

25:08.714 --> 25:10.558
I want you to focus on these scriptures here.

25:11.058 --> 25:17.650
It says here in Isaiah 41, 9, because I think these scriptures that I like can be your scriptures as well.

25:18.242 --> 25:21.426
because the devil is going to try to put fear on some of us at times in our lives.

25:21.887 --> 25:28.216
In Isaiah 41, 9, he said, you whom I have taken from the ends of the earth and called from its furthest regions.

25:28.236 --> 25:30.499
And I said to you, you are my servant.

25:30.920 --> 25:34.324
I have chosen you and I have not cast you away.

25:34.364 --> 25:40.172
I love that because God has chose you and he has not cast you away.

25:41.234 --> 25:44.178
Not only this, this is Old Testament.

25:44.450 --> 25:46.452
So you can go to the next level.

25:46.512 --> 25:49.055
We're not just servants of God, and we aren't.

25:49.135 --> 25:53.240
We serve God, but we're sons and daughters of the most high God.

25:54.021 --> 25:55.322
Can I get a witness in the house today?

25:55.702 --> 25:59.607
So he chose us to make us sons and daughters.

26:00.027 --> 26:04.292
You are a son and daughter of the most high God.

26:04.412 --> 26:04.752
Amen?

26:05.173 --> 26:05.874
Glory to God.

26:06.294 --> 26:07.275
So I love that.

26:07.355 --> 26:13.362
So the devil, when he puts fear on us, let's hone in on 4110,

26:13.570 --> 26:15.273
Fear not for I am with you.

26:15.313 --> 26:16.214
I say a 41 10.

26:16.314 --> 26:17.756
Fear not for I am with you.

26:18.317 --> 26:20.721
Be not dismayed for I am your God.

26:21.221 --> 26:22.363
I will strengthen you.

26:22.423 --> 26:24.126
Yes, I will help you.

26:24.146 --> 26:29.213
I will hold you with my righteous hand.

26:29.814 --> 26:30.355
Glory to God.

26:30.395 --> 26:30.976
I remember that.

26:31.396 --> 26:32.498
That scripture came to me.

26:33.119 --> 26:38.847
I remember that I was back at Rayma and we had this called this preaching workshop.

26:39.408 --> 26:43.474
And what it was was that they would have you preach in front of your classroom.

26:43.714 --> 26:47.219
And I did bad, I didn't do that well the first time I preached.

26:47.239 --> 26:48.981
They had you do it twice the second year.

26:49.602 --> 26:55.129
Some of the people had to add a strap to the chairs, keep them from falling over, amen, of fear, amen.

26:55.550 --> 27:03.881
Because it's fearful sometimes when you haven't done something and you're in front of people, you get nervous, amen.

27:04.482 --> 27:07.506
And so we developed this preaching workshop.

27:07.586 --> 27:14.854
And remember, we had like five or six people that we had to do a little preaching for 15 minutes in front of our colleagues.

27:15.335 --> 27:18.618
And I remember that it was my turn to do it on a Friday night.

27:19.179 --> 27:21.421
And we had it at a home.

27:21.902 --> 27:25.426
And I was nervous and God gave me this scripture, fear not, I am with you.

27:26.126 --> 27:26.387
Amen.

27:26.707 --> 27:33.074
So whatever fear that you're dealing with, it may seem small to you, but it can be big to somebody else.

27:33.858 --> 27:39.624
Your fear might, somebody else's fear might be small to you, but to you can be gigantic.

27:40.786 --> 27:41.126
Amen.

27:41.446 --> 27:44.470
And the devil wants that fear to be gigantic in your life.

27:44.870 --> 27:46.712
So fear not for I am with you.

27:46.772 --> 27:48.875
Be not dismayed for I am your God.

27:49.335 --> 27:50.417
I will strengthen you.

27:50.597 --> 27:51.658
Yes, I will help you.

27:51.678 --> 27:55.142
I will help hold you with my righteous right hand.

27:55.622 --> 28:02.450
So this tells me that God will strengthen us and help us in time and need and hold us in our trials of life.

28:02.818 --> 28:04.320
Now, let me make this statement.

28:04.420 --> 28:11.186
Don't put your faith in your ability to hold on to God, but put your faith in God's ability to hold on to you.

28:11.246 --> 28:13.469
That's a good statement.

28:14.029 --> 28:17.112
Don't put your faith in your ability.

28:17.192 --> 28:18.994
God, I can hold on to you.

28:19.014 --> 28:20.756
Oh, I'm holding on.

28:21.316 --> 28:22.818
Sometimes we say, how are you doing?

28:22.838 --> 28:26.442
I'm holding on for dear life, amen?

28:26.462 --> 28:27.242
I'm holding on.

28:27.543 --> 28:30.866
No, no, don't put your faith in your ability to hold on

28:31.042 --> 28:34.485
Put your faith in God's ability to hold you.

28:34.505 --> 28:41.152
In other words, we must shift our faith from our effort to God's power on our life.

28:41.913 --> 28:54.405
I remember there was a story of this military operation with the Navy, and I believe it was on a carrier, and they had these hot air balloons that they were showing off to the people.

28:54.926 --> 28:58.930
And one of the hot air balloons got unlatched from the carrier

28:59.234 --> 29:12.749
And there were people that were assigned to guard that hot air balloon and three or four people, they had ropes on this hot air balloon and it started going up and they were trying to hold it down and all the men went up with the hot air balloon.

29:13.850 --> 29:22.060
And as that balloon started going higher and higher, the men are dangling on this hot air balloon and it's going 100 feet, 200 feet, 300 feet.

29:22.420 --> 29:24.783
And the people are watching, they're saying, oh my Lord.

29:25.123 --> 29:27.826
And then the guys started dropping to their deaths.

29:28.738 --> 29:56.818
except for one guy and that guy was hanging in there and they kept going higher and higher now it's a thousand feet and they're all watching the crowds watching they're waiting for this man they said this man must have a awesome grip this man must must be holding on for dear life they were able to get another balloon up to to get to get that guy they were able to get to get this guy to rescue him and when they got to that balloon they found that that he wasn't holding on to the rope

29:56.898 --> 30:04.666
When that balloon came up, he took that rope, wrapped it around him, tied it, and he was just sitting back looking at the view.

30:06.849 --> 30:07.830
What am I saying to you?

30:08.310 --> 30:14.157
I'm saying you need to take the rope of faith, and you don't need to be holding on to the rope of faith in your life.

30:14.477 --> 30:17.020
You need to let that rope of faith hold on to you.

30:17.080 --> 30:23.447
And when that rope of faith holds on to you, you just sit back and enjoy the scenery.

30:24.208 --> 30:26.450
Can I get a witness house today?

30:26.818 --> 30:31.803
And that man was the smartest man there because he understood grace.

30:32.263 --> 30:39.710
Grace is God's rope of life holding you to the balloons of life that will try to take you away from the people of life.

30:39.750 --> 30:40.491
You believe that today?

30:41.071 --> 30:46.156
And so I want to focus on to this account of King Saul.

30:46.797 --> 30:49.659
And King Saul had some issues.

30:49.759 --> 30:52.042
Anybody know about King Saul, amen?

30:52.702 --> 30:56.786
And he had some issues and King Saul lost the kingship.

30:57.346 --> 31:00.290
He lost his kingship, he lost his place in God.

31:01.051 --> 31:04.596
And let's just look at this story and find out why he lost it.

31:04.997 --> 31:05.317
Amen?

31:05.738 --> 31:08.662
Because if we can find out why he lost it, you won't lose it.

31:09.302 --> 31:09.623
Amen?

31:09.903 --> 31:16.432
Because I want each one of you, I want each one of you obtaining all the highest that God has for you.

31:17.093 --> 31:20.678
And I don't want you guys for fitting any good that God has for you.

31:21.379 --> 31:26.386
And so it says, now first Samuel 15, 10, 11 says, now the word of the Lord came to Samuel saying,

31:26.594 --> 31:39.148
I greatly regret that I have set up Saul as king, for he has turned back from following me and has not performed my commandments and it grieved Samuel and he cried the Lord all night.

31:40.069 --> 31:46.476
So the Lord revealed to Samuel that Saul was disobeying God, wasn't obeying God.

31:47.197 --> 31:55.186
So in verse 12, so when Samuel rose up early in the morning to meet Saul, it was told Samuel saying Saul went to Carmel

31:55.298 --> 32:02.648
Indeed, he set up a monument for himself, and he's gone out around, passed by, and gone down to Gilga.

32:03.529 --> 32:11.260
And so we see here that Saul, he was so lifted up in pride, he was building monuments to himself.

32:11.320 --> 32:12.201
You gotta be careful.

32:12.662 --> 32:15.105
When you start setting up statues in your house for yourself.

32:17.128 --> 32:21.033
Because when pride comes, the fall comes.

32:21.053 --> 32:24.498
Don't start patting yourself on the back.

32:24.642 --> 32:27.265
and thinking that you're all that and a bag of chips.

32:27.606 --> 32:27.926
Amen?

32:28.286 --> 32:30.349
You're not all that and a bag of chips.

32:30.790 --> 32:32.231
God is all that, amen?

32:32.892 --> 32:38.099
And so Samuel, so Samuel confronts King Saul about his sin.

32:38.159 --> 32:43.505
And what Saul was supposed to do was he was supposed to take out the army of the Amalekites.

32:43.966 --> 32:53.938
He was supposed to destroy everything and all the sheep and the oxen and all that was supposed to go to sacrifices to the Lord.

32:54.114 --> 32:56.717
and the king decided to hold on to all that stuff.

32:57.698 --> 33:08.251
And Saul said to Samuel, and then he said, because Samuel confronts him in chapter 15, verse 20, and Saul said to Samuel, but I have obeyed the voice of the Lord.

33:09.173 --> 33:13.938
Sometimes when we half obey, we say, oh, but I did obey God, partially.

33:14.279 --> 33:17.002
You know, partial obedience is still disobedience.

33:18.404 --> 33:20.827
Oh, I'm going to, I know I'm stepping on toes this morning.

33:21.468 --> 33:23.410
Partial obedience

33:23.682 --> 33:25.925
as the same as disobedience.

33:26.727 --> 33:30.252
But I obeyed the voice of the Lord, and God on the mission in which the Lord sent me.

33:30.553 --> 33:33.637
And I brought back Agag, the king of Amalek.

33:34.018 --> 33:44.454
And I have utterly destroyed the Amalekites, but the people took the plunder, sheep and oxen, and the best things which should have been utterly destroyed to sacrifice the Lord your God in Gilgah.

33:45.075 --> 33:50.023
And King Saul deflected his sin on the people when he was in charge.

33:50.143 --> 33:50.463
Amen?

33:50.844 --> 33:52.306
He said, it's the people.

33:52.482 --> 33:56.368
See, sometimes we want to blame the people when we really need to look at ourselves.

33:57.510 --> 33:57.850
Amen.

33:58.491 --> 34:10.269
And then here, so Sarah said, has a Lord in 1522, has the Lord, has the Lord as great delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices or obeying the voice of the Lord.

34:10.549 --> 34:13.073
In other words, sometimes we'll say, Lord, I won't do this.

34:13.253 --> 34:16.838
I know you want me to do this, but I'll give a bigger offering.

34:16.858 --> 34:21.906
You know, just giving a bigger offering doesn't discount being disobedient to the Lord.

34:22.338 --> 34:22.758
Amen.

34:23.119 --> 34:26.683
And he says, to obey is better than sacrifice.

34:26.903 --> 34:27.443
Think about this.

34:27.884 --> 34:31.388
To obey is better sacrifice and a heed than the fat of rams.

34:32.228 --> 34:37.915
For rebellion is a sin of witchcraft and stubbornness is an iniquity of idolatry.

34:38.655 --> 34:40.657
Because you have rejected the word of Lord.

34:40.998 --> 34:44.421
He also rejected you from being king.

34:44.441 --> 34:46.584
Now we're going to focus on this.

34:46.624 --> 34:48.786
This is not a good story by the way.

34:49.218 --> 34:52.141
This is a learning story.

34:52.181 --> 34:53.722
It's something that we want to learn.

34:53.742 --> 34:59.888
So you can read the Old Testament and it's very straightforward and true.

35:00.589 --> 35:02.350
And God will tell off on His people.

35:03.191 --> 35:07.195
God's not going to just protect everybody's good in the Kingdom of God.

35:07.215 --> 35:10.438
No, some people make mistakes and they have to learn from their mistakes.

35:11.058 --> 35:14.141
And it's better to learn from other people's mistakes than from your own.

35:15.122 --> 35:19.186
I would say again, it's better to learn from other people's mistakes than your own.

35:19.554 --> 35:31.026
Then in 1 Samuel 15, 24, then Saul said to Samuel, I have sinned, for I have transgressed the command of the Lord and your words, because I feared the people and obeyed their voice.

35:31.086 --> 35:31.587
Notice that?

35:32.167 --> 35:33.949
He said that I have sinned, and why?

35:34.349 --> 35:38.233
Because he feared the people and he obeyed their voice.

35:38.273 --> 35:42.137
In other words, Saul was a people pleaser.

35:43.859 --> 35:46.482
And if you can't be a people pleaser,

35:46.786 --> 35:49.869
all the time and be a God pleaser at the same time.

35:50.690 --> 35:55.054
Because sometimes you're gonna have to say no to people when they want you to say yes.

35:55.895 --> 36:02.501
Sometimes people, maybe your old friends, they may want you to go out to a club and you say, I'm not going there anymore.

36:02.861 --> 36:10.148
Sometimes you might have to say no, not because you don't like them, but you've decided not to go down that road.

36:11.089 --> 36:16.274
In other words, you wanna honor God over people's opinions.

36:16.930 --> 36:17.331
Amen.

36:17.691 --> 36:23.920
The key to overcome fear of people is to honor God above people's opinions.

36:24.241 --> 36:24.621
Amen.

36:25.102 --> 36:26.183
Jesus put it this way.

36:26.244 --> 36:34.936
When people were afraid to acknowledge Jesus, Lord, do you know there's Christians out here and there are Christians that are saved, that are afraid to witness for the Lord.

